Task 1: Discover Exposed .env Files
Understanding .env File Risks
Environment files commonly contain:

Database credentials (DB_HOST, DB_PASSWORD)
API keys (STRIPE_SECRET_KEY, SENDGRID_API_KEY)
OAuth secrets (GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET)
Cloud provider credentials (AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID)
Authentication tokens (GITHUB_TOKEN)
When committed to repositories or exposed in CI/CD logs, these secrets enable unauthorized access.

